  "rationale": "<p>Choice D is correct. By definition <em>f</em>(15) = 6&middot;15<sup>-1</sup> = 6&middot;(1/15) = 6/15. Choice A treats the exponent of -1 as a multiplier (6&middot;-15). Choice B treats 6 as if it too has the -1 exponent. Choice C inverts the fraction (i.e., evaluates 15&middot;6<sup>-1</sup> by accident).</p>",
